---
import CardGrid from '../../../components/CardGrid.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

const featuredArchetypes = [
  {
    title: 'Gunslinger',
    summary: 'A mythic revolver knight, duelist, protector, and remnant of a fallen order.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/gunslinger/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Walker',
    summary: 'A road-wise traveler who senses doors, thinnies, paths, and impossible distances.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/walker/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Singer',
    summary: 'A voice of harmony, sorrow, command, healing, or destruction.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/singer/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Tech-Knight',
    summary: 'A scavenger-engineer, relic hacker, gadget fighter, and heir to the broken machines of the Old Ones.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/tech-knight/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Demon-Blooded',
    summary: 'A person marked by the Prim, demon blood, forbidden pact, or inherited corruption.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/demon-blooded/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Touch-Bearer',
    summary: 'A psychic, empath, seer, dreamer, telepath, or wounded soul marked by the Touch.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/touch-bearer/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Hemophage',
    summary: 'A blood-hungry survivor caught between predator, parasite, and person.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/hemophage/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Protocol Shell',
    summary: 'A machine relic from the Age Before, still walking after the world that made it died.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/protocol-shell/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Tongue of Discord',
    summary: 'A silver-tongued manipulator whose voice bends minds, allegiance, fear, and truth.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/tongue-of-discord/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
  {
    title: 'Shard-Bound',
    summary: 'A fractured soul carrying multiple selves, voices, spirits, past lives, or alien fragments.',
    href: '/player-guide/archetypes/shard-bound/',
    audience: 'player' as const,
  },
];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Archetypes"
  summary="Choose your class by fantasy, complexity, combat role, story pressure, and the kind of trouble you want ka to put in your hands."
  eyebrow="Player options"
  audience="player"
  ctaPrimary={{ label: 'Create Your Character', href: '/player-guide/character-creation/' }}
  ctaSecondary={{ label: 'Download Character Sheet', href: '/downloads/character-sheet.md' }}
>
  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="content-lead">
      In <strong>Ka-Tet: The Path of the Beam</strong>, character classes are called{' '}
      <strong>Archetypes</strong>. Your archetype is both your mechanical chassis and your dramatic
      angle. It tells the table what you are good at, what kind of danger follows you, and how the
      Beam has marked you.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some archetypes are straightforward: the <strong>Gunslinger</strong> shoots first, stands
      firm, and carries the burden of the old code. Others ask more from the player: the{' '}
      <strong>Singer</strong> manages songs and support magic, the <strong>Walker</strong> bends
      travel and distance, and the <strong>Shard-Bound</strong> shifts between inner selves.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pick the one that sounds fun to play in a fight and compelling to live with between fights.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Quick Advice</p>
      <p>
        For a first game or public demo, start with <strong>Gunslinger</strong>,{' '}
        <strong>Walker</strong>, <strong>Singer</strong>, <strong>Tech-Knight</strong>, or{' '}
        <strong>Touch-Bearer</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Save <strong>Hemophage</strong>, <strong>Tongue of Discord</strong>,{' '}
        <strong>Demon-Blooded</strong>, <strong>Protocol Shell</strong>, and{' '}
        <strong>Shard-Bound</strong> for players who want stronger story complications or more
        mechanical complexity.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">What An Archetype Gives You</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your Hit Die and starting Grit/HP</li>
        <li>Your primary stats and saving throw proficiencies</li>
        <li>Your starting weapons, armor, tools, and skills</li>
        <li>Your level 1 features and later subclass/path choice</li>
        <li>Your role in combat, travel, investigation, and ka-tet scenes</li>
        <li>The kind of moral or supernatural pressure the GM can bring into your story</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Comparison Table</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Archetype</th>
          <th>Complexity</th>
          <th>Primary Stats</th>
          <th>Hit Die</th>
          <th>Combat Role</th>
          <th>Story Pressure</th>
          <th>Best For</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Gunslinger</td><td>Medium</td><td>Dexterity, Wisdom</td><td>d10</td><td>Precision striker / ranged duelist</td><td>The old code, leadership, guilt</td><td>Iconic western action</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Walker</td><td>Medium-High</td><td>Wisdom, Constitution, Dexterity</td><td>d8</td><td>Mobile scout / survival guide</td><td>Thinny exposure, strange roads</td><td>Exploration and movement</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Singer</td><td>High</td><td>Charisma, Wisdom</td><td>d8</td><td>Support caster / controller</td><td>Voice, harmony, grief</td><td>Magic, support, and drama</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tech-Knight</td><td>Medium-High</td><td>Intelligence, Dexterity</td><td>d8</td><td>Gadget fighter / tech problem-solver</td><td>Relics, malfunction, repair</td><td>Tools, tech, tactical utility</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Demon-Blooded</td><td>High</td><td>Charisma, Constitution</td><td>d8</td><td>Blaster / wildcard</td><td>Corruption, temptation, Prim influence</td><td>Dangerous power</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Touch-Bearer</td><td>Medium-High</td><td>Wisdom, Charisma</td><td>d8</td><td>Psychic seer / mental support</td><td>Visions, empathy, overload</td><td>Prophecy and emotional insight</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hemophage</td><td>High</td><td>Charisma, Dexterity, Constitution</td><td>d10</td><td>Predator / self-healing skirmisher</td><td>Hunger, secrecy, restraint</td><td>Antiheroes and body horror</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Protocol Shell</td><td>Medium-High</td><td>Intelligence, Dexterity or Constitution</td><td>d8</td><td>Durable utility / support</td><td>Machine identity, memory fragments</td><td>Robots and relics</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tongue of Discord</td><td>High</td><td>Charisma, Wisdom</td><td>d8</td><td>Social controller / manipulator</td><td>Compulsion, lies, corruption</td><td>Social power and dangerous words</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Shard-Bound</td><td>Very High</td><td>Wisdom, Charisma, varies by Persona</td><td>d8</td><td>Adaptive switch-hitter</td><td>Fractured identity, inner conflict</td><td>Experienced players who like complexity</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Choose By Playstyle</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Shoot, duel, protect, and lead:</strong> Gunslinger</li>
      <li><strong>Survive the road, read the land, and keep the party moving:</strong> Walker</li>
      <li><strong>Heal, inspire, calm madness, or fight with music:</strong> Singer</li>
      <li><strong>Repair old machines, use gadgets, and solve tech problems:</strong> Tech-Knight</li>
      <li><strong>Wield forbidden power with a cost:</strong> Demon-Blooded</li>
      <li><strong>See visions, sense danger, and read emotional truth:</strong> Touch-Bearer</li>
      <li><strong>Play a monster trying not to become one:</strong> Hemophage</li>
      <li><strong>Play a machine relic with lost directives and strange memory:</strong> Protocol Shell</li>
      <li><strong>Weaponize speech, lies, command, and fear:</strong> Tongue of Discord</li>
      <li><strong>Play multiple selves inside one body:</strong> Shard-Bound</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If someone asks to play a <strong>Breaker</strong>, the safest player-facing answer is: use
      <strong> Touch-Bearer</strong> unless the GM has approved a special Breaker build. Breakers
      are usually stronger as NPCs or narrative-tier psychics.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Archetype Cards</p>
    <CardGrid cards={featuredArchetypes} />
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Archetype Snapshots</p>

    <h2>Gunslinger</h2>
    <p>
      A mythic revolver knight, duelist, protector, and remnant of a fallen order. Play a
      Gunslinger if you want iconic western action, grim codes of honor, and a clear combat anchor
      for the ka-tet.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> Medium</li>
      <li><strong>Hit Die:</strong> d10</li>
      <li><strong>Primary Stats:</strong> Dexterity and Wisdom</li>
      <li><strong>Combat Role:</strong> Precision striker, ranged duelist, battlefield leader</li>
      <li><strong>Story Pressure:</strong> The old code, leadership, violence, guilt</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Walker</h2>
    <p>
      A road-wise traveler who senses doors, thinnies, paths, and impossible distances. Play a
      Walker if you want to be the person who gets the group where it needs to go when the road
      stops making sense.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> Medium-High</li>
      <li><strong>Hit Die:</strong> d8</li>
      <li><strong>Primary Stats:</strong> Wisdom and Constitution</li>
      <li><strong>Combat Role:</strong> Mobile skirmisher, survival support, terrain controller</li>
      <li><strong>Story Pressure:</strong> Thinny exposure, strange roads, impossible choices</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Singer</h2>
    <p>
      A voice of harmony, sorrow, command, healing, or destruction. Play a Singer if you want
      bard-style magic with darker resonance, emotional scenes, and support power that feels mythic.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> High</li>
      <li><strong>Hit Die:</strong> d8</li>
      <li><strong>Primary Stats:</strong> Charisma and Wisdom</li>
      <li><strong>Combat Role:</strong> Support caster, healer, controller, morale engine</li>
      <li><strong>Story Pressure:</strong> Voice, emotion, healing, harmony, grief</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tech-Knight</h2>
    <p>
      A scavenger-engineer, relic hacker, gadget fighter, and heir to the broken machines of the
      Old Ones. Play a Tech-Knight if you like tools, repairs, drones, gadgets, and old-world
      science-fantasy utility.
    </p>

    <h2>Demon-Blooded</h2>
    <p>
      A person marked by the Prim, demon blood, forbidden pact, or inherited corruption. Choose
      this if you want dangerous power, visible cost, and a character who gives the GM permission
      to tempt, haunt, or corrupt them.
    </p>

    <h2>Touch-Bearer</h2>
    <p>
      A psychic, empath, seer, dreamer, telepath, or wounded soul marked by the Touch. Choose this
      if you want visions, empathy, emotional insight, and story-facing psychic pressure.
    </p>

    <h2>Hemophage</h2>
    <p>
      A blood-hungry survivor caught between predator, parasite, and person. Choose this if you
      want stealth, hunger, self-healing, secrecy, and body-horror antihero pressure.
    </p>

    <h2>Protocol Shell</h2>
    <p>
      A machine relic from the Age Before, still walking after the world that made it died. Choose
      this if you want a robot or artificial person whose directives, memory fragments, and
      personhood become part of the drama.
    </p>

    <h2>Tongue of Discord</h2>
    <p>
      A silver-tongued manipulator whose voice bends minds, allegiance, fear, and truth. Choose
      this if you want words to be your main weapon and are comfortable with morally dangerous
      influence.
    </p>

    <h2>Shard-Bound</h2>
    <p>
      A fractured soul carrying multiple selves, voices, spirits, past lives, or alien fragments.
      Choose this only if you want a high-complexity role with serious internal conflict and
      mechanical tracking.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Archetype Selection By Party Role</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Combat Anchor:</strong> Gunslinger, Hemophage, Tech-Knight, Demon-Blooded</li>
        <li><strong>Support and Healing:</strong> Singer, Touch-Bearer, Caretaker-style Protocol Shell</li>
        <li><strong>Exploration and Travel:</strong> Walker, Tech-Knight, Touch-Bearer, Protocol Shell</li>
        <li><strong>Social and Intrigue:</strong> Singer, Tongue of Discord, Charm-style Protocol Shell</li>
        <li><strong>Horror and Psychic Play:</strong> Touch-Bearer, Shard-Bound, Demon-Blooded, Hemophage</li>
        <li><strong>Beginner-Friendly Picks:</strong> Gunslinger, Walker, Tech-Knight</li>
        <li><strong>Best for Experienced Players:</strong> Singer, Demon-Blooded, Hemophage, Protocol Shell, Tongue of Discord, Shard-Bound</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Archetype Selection By Primary Stat</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Dexterity-focused:</strong> Gunslinger, Walker, Tech-Knight, Hemophage</li>
        <li><strong>Wisdom-focused:</strong> Walker, Singer, Touch-Bearer, Shard-Bound, Gunslinger</li>
        <li><strong>Charisma-focused:</strong> Singer, Demon-Blooded, Tongue of Discord, Hemophage</li>
        <li><strong>Intelligence-focused:</strong> Tech-Knight, Protocol Shell, Shard-Bound</li>
        <li><strong>Constitution-focused:</strong> Walker, Hemophage, Demon-Blooded, defensive Protocol Shells</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Recommended Starting Stat Arrays</p>
    <p>
      These are quick recommendations for players using the 27-point stat-buy system from the
      Character Creation page.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Archetype</th>
          <th>Suggested Starting Scores</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Gunslinger</td><td>10, 15, 14, 10, 14, 8</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Walker</td><td>10, 13, 15, 10, 14, 8</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Singer</td><td>8, 12, 13, 10, 14, 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tech-Knight</td><td>8, 14, 13, 15, 10, 10</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Demon-Blooded</td><td>8, 12, 14, 10, 10, 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Touch-Bearer</td><td>8, 12, 13, 14, 15, 10</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hemophage</td><td>10, 15, 14, 8, 10, 13</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Protocol Shell</td><td>8, 14, 13, 15, 10, 10</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tongue of Discord</td><td>8, 12, 13, 10, 14, 15</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Shard-Bound</td><td>8, 13, 12, 14, 15, 10</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      These arrays are defaults, not hard rules. A Shard-Bound’s exact stats may vary by Persona,
      and a Protocol Shell’s secondary stats may shift by directive.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="section-label">Next Steps</p>
    <CardGrid
      cards={[
        {
          title: 'Character Creation',
          summary: 'Assign stats, choose a background, calculate Grit, and bind yourself to the ka-tet.',
          href: '/player-guide/character-creation/',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Ka Points',
          summary: 'Learn the signature fate mechanic that keeps the story moving.',
          href: '/player-guide/rules/ka-points/',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Downloads',
          summary: 'Grab the character sheet, quickstart, and public-facing play aids.',
          href: '/downloads/',
          audience: 'public',
        },
        {
          title: 'Pre-Generated Characters',
          summary: 'See ready-to-play characters for demos and low-prep first sessions.',
          href: '/pregens/',
          audience: 'public',
        },
      ]}
    />
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
